`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
**Why `position: relative` on the cards wrapper?** The `dropLineStyle()` returns an absolutely-positioned 2px indigo line. It needs a positioned ancestor to anchor against — that wrapper div is its containing block. Without it, the drop indicator would position relative to some distant ancestor and appear in the wrong spot.

**Why `useDragReorder` is generic** — the hook takes `T[]` and `onChange(T[])`, so it works identically for shadows, transitions, and now transforms. The reorder logic (splice from old index, insert at new index) is the same; only the row rendering differs.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

